HEADWORD: Borsholder
<hw>Bors"hold`er</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OE.
<ets>borsolder</ets>; prob. fr. AS. <ets>borg</ets>, gen.
<ets>borges</ets>, pledge + <ets>ealdor</ets> elder. See
<er>Borrow</er>, and <er>Elder</er>, <pos>a.</pos>]</ety> <fld>(Eng.
Law)</fld> <def>The head or chief of a tithing, or borough (see 2d
<er>Borough</er>); the headborough; a parish constable.</def>
<rj><au>Spelman.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
